Risk 3 – Positive Risk (Opportunity)

Problem Statement
The demand for disability management services, workplace wellness programs, and employee health solutions is increasing across Canada. This creates a valuable opportunity for Canada Life to grow its customer base and strengthen its presence in the healthcare market.

Risk Statement
As more organizations invest in disability management and workplace wellness services, Canada Life has an opportunity to increase its market share, generate higher revenue, and improve its competitive position.

Impact Statement
If Canada Life successfully takes advantage of this growing demand, it can attract new customers, strengthen relationships with existing clients, increase revenue, and enhance its reputation in the healthcare and insurance sectors.
Key Risk Indicator (KRI): Market Growth Rate

Level	Threshold
Green	Market growth above 8%
Amber	Market growth between 5% and 8%
Red	Market growth below 5%
Conclusion

The acquisition of Santé Circle Health presents both challenges and opportunities for Canada Life. On one hand, increasing competition from digital healthcare providers and aggressive pricing strategies could put pressure on growth and profitability.

